headline: The potential this strategist sees in small-cap bank stocks
summary: US stocks (^DJI, ^IXIC, ^GSPC) closed Tuesday's trading higher, the Dow Jones Industrial Average closing above 49,000 for the second session in a row. Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton speaks with Commerce Street Holdings CEO Dory Wiley about his outlook on small-cap and regional bank stocks. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
